# Sub-PR design discipline

Multi-round per-trait PRs (RandomX v2 sub-PRs, LWMA-1 Phase 4,
future consensus-critical extractions) accumulate process disciplines
that are not trait-specific. Phase 2c's design rounds (1–5) and
impl-time pre-flight (Round 0, R0-D5–R0-D12) produced fourteen
named disciplines; they first landed in
`docs/design/RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` and
`docs/design/RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_AUDIT.md` and are promoted here so
downstream authors inherit them without re-deriving from one plan-doc.

**Disposition choice.** Option A — this file — over
`docs/conventions/SUB_PR_DESIGN_DISCIPLINE.md`. The disciplines fit
the project's standard rules shape (rejection + reopening criteria +
re-evaluation shape + anti-patterns + precedents) without needing a
separate multi-page conventions doc. Worked examples cite the 2c
plan-doc and audit trail; the rule is the authoritative surface.

Per `05-system-thinking.mdc`, these disciplines are the operational
form of "specification first, code second" for sub-PR design: the
spec is the frozen contract, the threat-model frame, and the substrate
read — not prose intuition about what the reference "probably" does.

## Scope

Applies when a work item is split across multiple short-lived PRs
with design rounds before implementation cuts — especially when
consensus behavior, FFI boundaries, or inherited reference ports are
involved. Does not replace trait-specific plan-docs; those carry the
substrate enumeration. This rule carries the *process* that plan-docs
should follow.

## Round 0 — impl-time pre-flight shape

Every multi-round per-trait PR inherits a **Round 0** pass between
design closure and production code:

1. **Substrate re-check.** Re-read the substrate each closed
   disposition cites (source files at audit pin, call graphs, cost
   profiles, established conventions). Catches falsified-justification
   and implicitly-committed-shape dispositions before code lands.
2. **Artifact execution.** Run the tests, benches, and generators the
   plan-doc prescribes; reconcile measurements against budgets at
   PR-open. Catches findings substrate re-read alone cannot surface
   (R0-D10–D12 precedents).

Round 0 is **not a redesign**. It is a discipline pass that catches
design-time decisions falsified by impl-time substrate or by running
produced artifacts. Record findings in the plan-doc status block and
in a sibling audit trail (2c's shape:
`docs/design/<TRAIT>_AUDIT.md`).

**Posture (extends Round 4 / Round 5).** Design closure means
**design closure plus active defense against named attacker
objectives**, not per-finding whack-a-mole. Round 0 complements the
threat-model frame: substrate re-check defends against transcription
and scope drift; artifact execution defends against estimates that
never met measurement.

