## Part A — Design-round disciplines

These emerge from adversarial design rounds before implementation.
Apply at round closure and when scoping the next sub-PR.

### A1. Function-body replacement contract

**One-line shape.** Freeze signature + caller state fields + dispatch
input fields; land a NOP or `unimplemented!()` body; the next sub-PR
replaces the body in place only.

**Rejection.** Trait + stub-impl, or signature churn between "extract
surface" and "implement surface," decouples review properties and
invites silent contract drift (new parameters, return values, state
fields added when the body lands).

**Reopening criteria.** Reopen the frozen signature when a downstream
sub-PR's benchmarks or threat-model review shows the single-pass (or
current) shape cannot meet a load-bearing budget **and** profiling
attributes the shortfall to the frozen shape itself — not to missing
implementation. Example: 2c locked single-pass `dispatch_instruction`;
reopen to IBC two-pass only if 2d benchmarks show single-pass cannot
hit the Phase 0 budget and profiling attributes shortfall to per-call
decode cost (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` §5.1.1).

**Re-evaluation shape.** New design-round entry in the downstream
sub-PR's plan-doc naming the frozen surface violated, substrate
evidence (bench profile, threat-model finding), and the amended
contract. Implementation follows in a separate commit sequence per
`90-commits.mdc`.

**Anti-patterns.**

- **"We'll fix the signature when we implement."** The body-replacement
  PR's review surface becomes diff-archaeology instead of mechanical
  contract check.
- **Mock trait for one implementation.** Trait with one impl is debt
  per `21-reversion-clause-discipline.mdc`; use function-body
  replacement instead (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` §5.1 F1 / R2-D1).

**Precedents.**

- `dispatch_instruction(instr: &Instruction, state: &mut VmState)` —
  NOP body in 2c (PR #66), body replacement in 2d
  (`docs/design/RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` §5.1.1;
  `docs/design/RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2D_PLAN.md` §1).
- F4 absorption: `compute_hash(&Cache, …)` production signature lands
  in 2c; no `DatasetReader` trait + mock
  (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` §5.4).

---

### A2. Audit-against-actual-code

**One-line shape.** Plan-doc audit tables cite pinned line ranges; the
load-bearing step is reading source at those lines, not producing a
plausible table from intuition.

**Rejection.** Audit tables filled from prompted lists, documentation
summaries, or training-data recall without line-range evidence. A
table without citations is a claim that no audit happened.

**Reopening criteria.** Not applicable as a standing rejection — the
discipline is always load-bearing for consensus-critical ports.
**Relaxation** (using uncited tables for non-consensus internal
refactors) reopens only when the changed surface has zero
consensus-affecting consumers and the PR's reviewer-map documents
that exclusion per `07-consensus-atomic-cutovers.mdc` criterion 4.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Reviewer spot-checks cited file at pinned
commit; row fails if cited lines do not support the disposition.
Round 5 formalized **show your work**: every row names
`path/to/source:N–M` at the audit pin (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md`
§5.11.8).

**Anti-patterns.**

- **"The table looks plausible."** The mp failure mode: Rounds 1–2
  had `mp` as a `VmState` field; reading `vm_interpreted.cpp:89`
  showed it is a v2-only local alias for `mem.ma` (R3-D1).
- **"We caught one bug, audit done."** R5-D1 reframes: the failure
  mode is skipping reading-the-source — the table is output, not
  substance (`16-architectural-inheritance.mdc` §"audits-are-clean-so-
  compress").

**Precedents.**

- R3-D1 `mp` correction (`vm_interpreted.cpp:89`; not a struct field)
  — consensus-split source if shipped (`§5.11.8`).
- R1-D3 (2d Round 1): wire opcodes are frequency-encoded
  (`bytecode_machine.hpp:67–98`), not `InstructionType` enum values
  (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2D_PLAN.md` §3.5 R1-D3).
- Round 0 F3: CFROUND throttle vs non-existent imm32 cap — cited
  `bytecode_machine.hpp:261–266`, not a prompted wrong row
  (`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_AUDIT.md` §Round 0).

