## Part B — Impl-time pre-flight disciplines (Round 0)

These emerge when design-closed dispositions meet the actual substrate
or produced artifacts. Apply during Round 0 before production commits.

### B1. Test-fidelity vs dominant-cost (R0-D5)

**Rejection.** Test-only API surfaces (`Cache::from_raw`, fast-path
constructors) justified by per-test execution savings when build
dominates wall clock (≫100×) or the optimization breaks test meaning
(T1' must call real `Cache::derive`).

**Reopening criteria.** Reintroduce a test-only fast path when
measurement shows the optimized path is load-bearing against the
**dominant** cost (e.g., CI execution budget, not local dev build)
**and** the test's fidelity claim remains true.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Round 0 finding in plan-doc + audit trail;
LoC/commit table updates; reversion clause in §5.9 narrative.

**Anti-pattern.** "Saves 200ms per test" under 15-minute builds.

**Precedent.** `Cache::from_raw` dropped — T2 shares one derive per
`#[test]`; T1'a needs 100 real derives (`§14` R0-D5; PR #66).

---

### B2. Tests-use-the-actual-API (R0-D6)

**Rejection.** Widening `pub` surface, test-only accessors, or
visibility relaxations so integration tests can read internal state.

**Reopening criteria.** New `pub` test-only API reopens only with a
**named production caller** documented in the same PR — not test
convenience alone.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Relocate tests to `src/*.rs#mod tests` with
`include_bytes!` fixtures (Phase 2a/2b convention); update plan-doc
test placement paragraphs.

**Anti-pattern.** Integration tests forcing `pub fn memory(&self)` on
`Cache` for byte equality.

**Precedent.** T1–T8 moved from `tests/{cache,vm}/*.rs` to unit
tests in `src/cache.rs` / `src/vm.rs` (`§14` R0-D6).

---

### B3. Call-graph-anchored visibility (R0-D7)

**Rejection.** `pub(crate)` (or `pub`) promotion for helpers with no
direct caller — optionality without named caller per
`21-reversion-clause-discipline.mdc`.

**Reopening criteria.** Promotion when a **direct call site** lands in
production code (not transitive consumption through another entry
point); design-round 1 of the introducing PR documents call-graph
evidence.

**Re-evaluation shape.** §4.1 dependency table row rewrite with
withdrawn promotion + reopening criterion.

**Anti-pattern.** "2c promotes so cache can call it" when
`derive_item` → `execute_superscalar` → `IMUL_RCP` arm consumes the
reciprocal transitively (`superscalar.rs:1463`).

**Precedent.** `randomx_reciprocal` stays private (`§14` R0-D7;
`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_AUDIT.md` §4 row 2).

---

### B4. Results-fidelity over shape-fidelity (R0-D8)

**Rejection.** 1:1 ports of reference method counts, class shapes, or
intermediate fields when target-language fusion produces the same
byte-identical results with cleaner ownership.

**Reopening criteria.** Literal shape port when fusion **provably**
changes consensus bytes (not merely diverges from C layout) — reopen
via design-round with spec-vector evidence.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Plan-doc names C shape vs Rust shape side
by side; frozen field sets unchanged if results-equivalent.

**Anti-pattern.** Artificial `Program.entropy_buffer` field to mirror
C's `generateProgram` + `initialize` split.

**Precedent.** C three-method init → Rust `init_scratchpad` +
`init_program` fusion (`§14` R0-D8; `vm_interpreted.cpp:50–54` vs
`vm.rs`).

---

### B5. Per-commit build cleanliness (R0-D8 sibling)

**Rejection.** `include_bytes!` to fixtures before the generator commit
that produces them; commit sequence that breaks `cargo build` at
intermediate SHAs.

**Reopening criteria.** Fixture-before-generator only when fixtures are
**checked in unchanged** from a prior phase and commit table cites
their provenance — not for new vectors.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Defer spec-vector tests to generator commit;
add fixture-free property tests (T3'–T8') in earlier commits per
§5.11.1 pattern.

**Anti-pattern.** §9 titles "(T3–T5)" in commit 5 while F6 generator
lands commit 7.

**Precedent.** T3–T8 spec vectors deferred to commit 7; T3'–T8' in
commits 5–6 (`§14` R0-D8).

---

### B6. Numeric-constant verification (R0-D9)

**Rejection.** Numeric values in plan-doc tables transcribed without
reading the cited substrate line — conflating adjacent constants
(`PROGRAM_ITERATIONS` 2048 vs `PROGRAM_SIZE` 384).

**Reopening criteria.** N/A — always verify. Table rows that cite
`configuration.h:N` must have the value column checked against line N
at audit pin.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Plan-doc errata + fix-up commit for code
already landed with wrong constant; separate commits per
`90-commits.mdc`.

**Anti-pattern.** F5 row filled from intuition while column 1 cites
the correct line (R0-D2 citation correct, R0-D9 value wrong).

**Precedent.** `PROGRAM_SIZE = 384`, `PROGRAM_ITERATIONS = 2048`
(`configuration.h:57`, `:62`; commit `186a8cfdf` fix).

---

### B7. Cross-language implicit-state-loss (R0-D10)

**Rejection.** Fusing two reference storage shapes into one Rust field
without explicit assertions for behaviors that fell out of the
reference's separate lifetimes (default init, per-scope reset).

**Reopening criteria.** Omit explicit reset only with proof that Rust
type's default or drop semantics match reference per-scope behavior
for **all** entry points — including nested calls tests do not cover.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Comment block naming C semantics + explicit
reset at equivalent transition; extend T8-style cross-boundary tests.

**Anti-pattern.** Assuming `VmState::new` zeroing `r` covers inter-
chain carryover inside `compute_hash`.

**Precedent.** `self.r = [0; 8]` at `execute_program` entry — C fresh
`NativeRegisterFile` per chain (`vm_interpreted.cpp`; T8 caught
carryover T6/T7 missed) (`§14` R0-D10).

---

### B8. Storage-format divergence — byte vs result equivalence (R0-D11)

**Rejection.** Treating byte-identical serialization as required when
spec demands result-equivalence only; or fixing Rust to match C
generator artifact when reference post-processing is optimization, not
consensus semantics.

**Reopening criteria.** Byte-equality requirement when a downstream
consumer hashes or persists the intermediate representation on-chain
or in consensus — documented in plan-doc with consumer cite.

**Re-evaluation shape.** Fix generator or test oracle, not port, when
Rust results-equivalent path is spec-faithful; record in audit trail.

**Anti-pattern.** Changing Rust `IMUL_RCP` storage to match C side-
cache index when interpreter computes reciprocal on the fly and T2
proves item parity.

**Precedent.** T1 generator bypasses `initCache` IMUL_RCP post-process;
Rust stores original `imm32` (`dataset.cpp:131–138` vs
`superscalar.rs:1465–1467`) (`§14` R0-D11).

---

### B9. Plan-author-estimate vs empirical measurement (R0-D12)

**Rejection.** Absolute PR-gate thresholds set from estimates without
measurement on implementation hardware; treating plan-doc budget as
gate when bench function measures a wider surface than budget text
describes.

**Reopening criteria.** Threshold revision when (a) optimization lands
with measured delta against recorded baseline, (b) workload amortization
changes what the budget measures (e.g., LRU cache hit rate), or (c)
downstream phase adds sub-bench that isolates the bounded portion.

**Re-evaluation shape.** `BENCH_RESULTS.md` §Measurements + §Threshold
reconciliation with named reopening criteria; forward to downstream
§13 if not blocking current PR.

**Anti-pattern.** Blocking merge on 100 µs gate when bench calls full
`compute_hash` (~296 ms median under stub-NOP).

**Precedent.** `cache_derive` 341 ms vs 200 ms budget; `compute_hash_alloc`
296 ms vs 100 µs label mismatch (`BENCH_RESULTS.md`; `§14` R0-D12).

